18
00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:50.670
for that let us consider 3 typical examples

19
00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:58.680
first example is very simple, low degree, simple coefficients

20
00:01:58.690 --> 00:02:06.690
second example, still low degree, but more complex coefs

21
00:02:06.700 --> 00:02:18.200
finally third example, really complicated with a high degree (9), and many non-null coefs

22
00:02:18.210 --> 00:02:23.210
What questions can we ask ourselves ?

23
00:02:23.220 --> 00:02:30.220
are we able to solve these equations using only the 4 operations, and nested roots

24
00:02:30.230 --> 00:02:37.730
and if so, which is the simplest to solve, which is the hardest

25
